            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1599748949089-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the lean beef mince has browned, add the <strong>diced pepper</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>ginger</strong> to the pan and cook for 2 min further</p><p>Reduce the heat to medium and add your<strong> Chinese rice wine</strong>,<strong> hoisin sauce</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame oil</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until thickened, sticky and the beef is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your<strong> Chinese-style lean beef & green pepper stir-fry</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1599748960712-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
